These menu options define the section planes in which 
the solution will be drawn with a color function of solution values
from minimum BLUE to maximum MAGENTA
(several planes may be simultaneously drawn)

1 : X=Constant  Drawn of solution section from X=CT planes
2 : Y=Constant  Drawn of solution section from Y=CT planes
3 : Z=Constant  Drawn of solution section from Z=CT planes
                Default option

4 : a PLANE to define
A PLANE defined by the input of 3 POINTS not on a same straight line

5 : COLOR of Boundary EDGES
To define the color of boundary edges to locate them

6 : DRAWING TYPE of Boundary EDGES
continuous line or dotted line to draw the boundary edges

7 : COLOR of EDGES on SECTION PLANES
to see the intersection of sections and the mesh

8 : DRAWING TYPE of EDGES on SECTION PLANES
continuous line or dotted line to draw the edges in section planes

11: NUMBER of PLANES   Default value=1

12: Regular DISTANCE between MIN-MAX
The object COORDINATES MIN and MAX are computed
The constant coordinate of the i-th drawn PLANE will be
      MIN + (i-1)*(MAX-MIN)/(number of PLANES-1)

13: Give the COORDINATE MIN & MAX of PLANES
Then, the constant coordinate of the i-th drawn PLANE will be
      MIN + (i-1)*(MAX-MIN)/(number of PLANES-1)

14: Give the COORDINATE of each PLANE

15: AMPLIFICATION coefficient
This coefficient multiply the value of the solution
in the normal direction

19: REDUCTION % of FACES
to see better the position of edges of faces
or to see the interior of the materials or the other side

80: INITIATE AGAIN the data of PLANES
to suppress the old definitions of planes
and define new planes

90: EXECUTION of the DRAWING
Draw with the drawing characteristics defined before
planes, colors, type of lines, ...
